Well, on my site-- I came
up with this too late for it

00:46:05.856 --> 00:46:07.480
to be in the book,
so it's on my site--

00:46:07.480 --> 00:46:10.010
I have a checklist
for habit change.

00:46:10.010 --> 00:46:14.420
And so the idea is you could
put the habit that you want,

00:46:14.420 --> 00:46:16.600
and then you could go
through and generate ideas

00:46:16.600 --> 00:46:18.567
based on all the 21 strategies.

00:46:18.567 --> 00:46:20.900
And so first of all, when
you're trying to form a habit,

00:46:20.900 --> 00:46:22.690
you want it to be as
specific as possible.

00:46:22.690 --> 00:46:24.900
So you wouldn't want to
form the habit of being fit.

00:46:24.900 --> 00:46:26.300
Obviously, that's a description.

00:46:26.300 --> 00:46:27.674
But you'd want to
be like, I want

00:46:27.674 --> 00:46:29.730
to have the habit of
going for a run every day.

00:46:29.730 --> 00:46:34.010
Or I want to have the
habit of walking to work

00:46:34.010 --> 00:46:35.500
or whatever it might be.

00:46:35.500 --> 00:46:37.850
And then you can go through
all the 21 strategies

00:46:37.850 --> 00:46:40.350
and figure out, how can I
make this more convenient?

00:46:40.350 --> 00:46:42.790
How can I make it more
inconvenient to do

00:46:42.790 --> 00:46:43.490
the opposite?

00:46:43.490 --> 00:46:47.200
How can I use pairing, which is
when you do two things at once?

00:46:47.200 --> 00:46:49.619
How can I give myself
healthy treats that

00:46:49.619 --> 00:46:50.910
are going to keep me energized?

00:46:50.910 --> 00:46:54.850
How can I think about
being with other people?

00:46:54.850 --> 00:46:56.350
How can I think
about my tendencies?

00:46:56.350 --> 00:46:59.130
So when it comes to
fitness, some obligers

00:46:59.130 --> 00:47:01.060
have told me
hilarious strategies

00:47:01.060 --> 00:47:03.050
that they've used for fitness.

00:47:03.050 --> 00:47:06.350
My favorite, two obligers
decided that they

00:47:06.350 --> 00:47:07.840
would be workout buddies.

00:47:07.840 --> 00:47:11.470
And at the end of the workout,
they each trade a shoe.

00:47:11.470 --> 00:47:13.580
So if you don't come
tomorrow, I can't work out

00:47:13.580 --> 00:47:14.850
because you've got my shoe.

00:47:14.850 --> 00:47:17.255
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:17.255 --> 00:47:19.050
You have to come!

00:47:19.050 --> 00:47:20.830
So there's a lot of
things like that.

00:47:20.830 --> 00:47:21.700
But it's like this.

00:47:21.700 --> 00:47:23.960
For a rebel, that
would them not go.

00:47:23.960 --> 00:47:26.240
Because they'd be like, no
one can tell me what to do.

00:47:26.240 --> 00:47:28.573
I'm not going to just because
it's inconvenient for you,

00:47:28.573 --> 00:47:30.240
because I don't feel like it.

00:47:30.240 --> 00:47:32.540
And so for them, that
would be counterproductive.

00:47:32.540 --> 00:47:36.290
So it's again figuring out well,
what's going to work for me?

00:47:36.290 --> 00:47:39.522
Or a questioner might
be like well, I'm

00:47:39.522 --> 00:47:41.105
supposed to be doing
this gym routine,

00:47:41.105 --> 00:47:42.420
but I'm not convinced
it's the best for me.

00:47:42.420 --> 00:47:43.920
I really need to
put it in the time.

00:47:43.920 --> 00:47:45.620
The desire to make
an Excel spreadsheet

00:47:45.620 --> 00:47:49.330
is a very big tip off that
someone's a questioner.

00:47:49.330 --> 00:47:51.750
And you know, I had a
friend who was a questioner

00:47:51.750 --> 00:47:53.920
and she wanted to start
eating more healthily.

00:47:53.920 --> 00:47:55.420
And she interviewed
10 nutritionists

00:47:55.420 --> 00:47:57.794
and had an Excel spreadsheet
and ranked them on a 1 to 10

00:47:57.794 --> 00:48:00.330
scale on seven
different questions.

00:48:00.330 --> 00:48:03.380
And then she believed, really
believed in what she was doing.

00:48:03.380 --> 00:48:04.921
And then she was
able to stick to it.

00:48:04.921 --> 00:48:06.400
So again, a
questioner might say,

00:48:06.400 --> 00:48:08.290
I'm going to look at these seven
different types of exercise

00:48:08.290 --> 00:48:09.770
and decide which
is the one that's

00:48:09.770 --> 00:48:12.710
going to do for me what I want
in the most efficient, best use

00:48:12.710 --> 00:48:14.240
of my time way.

00:48:14.240 --> 00:48:15.600
And really put the time in.

00:48:15.600 --> 00:48:17.590
Because a lot of times,
when questioners can't

00:48:17.590 --> 00:48:19.595
do something-- like a
questioner was like,

00:48:19.595 --> 00:48:20.980
